<br>
I'm on a blue server, so my knowledge on pvp is next to nil, but then again, I don't pvp.<br>
<br>
I checked out this thread on EQlive called <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=1011" target="top">&quot;Bards - Nerf or Not&quot;.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
I don't understand how nerfing selos, manadrain and offensive songs will &quot;fix&quot; anything.<br>
<br>
I'm a time flagged, Ep geared bard. I have no offensive aas (Guild wanted me to get mod,jf and defensive aas), and I've never set foot in Vex Thal (I'd rather gouge my eyes out with car keys then try and get myself keyed). I have no Manadrain (never for sale), and No ancient mezz.<br>
<br>
Whenever I duel I wonder how the hell am I going to do anything dangerous. I can't land dots on anyone, dispell is canceled via instaclicks, SoS does damage way to slow, and I parse maybe ~40 dps with melee. So ussauly I run around looking pretty.<br>
<br>
Which brings me to my point, how am I overpowered? Is it my inability to die? (Aside from HT or MB I guess). My uber Melee dps?<br>
<br>
Surely theres other bards on pvp servers like me!? Because unless I'm missing something, two songs shouldn't mean the difference between suck and overpowered.<br>
<br>
Please help inform the uninformed! (if this is in the wrong spot, feel free to move it) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lanolar>Lanolar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 954<br> <font color=#330000>(7/1/04 1:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19557.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Folks on EQlive make me /boggle</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Is it my inability to die?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
