<br>
Chill people.<br>
<br>
Anyway the core of the argument on bard pvp is  team pvp, not duels.<br>
<br>
Duels rely on the skills only one class possesses to win, bards really suck at damage plain and simple. I could care less how many clueless chanters care to try and refute me but if you think I can kill anything remotely the same in levels and gear in pvp with chants, you are on drugs.<br>
<br>
The way bards duel really against a similarly geared and smart player is the sleep principle as mearis himself so kindly belabored the other month. I mean by running the other person around so long they just say &quot;ok screw this, you win&quot;.<br>
<br>
By this I mean no point using mez, bards don't need that to live it's merely a crutch. Bards have enough tools at their disposal to live though anything another player can dish out given enough room. <br>
<br>
I liken it to mental attrition and as a fan of history 1914-1918 I can appreciate the tactic. I'm morbid that way =p<br>
<br>
<br>
So then what is the point of all those whining people? Bards are the NUMBER ONE support class bar none. <br>
<br>
List it off, group resists to 500 easy as well as group wide  selo, haste, focus, ds, regen hp, regen mana, lev, REFLECT , shadowstep etc ad nausium. We cure targeted, we debuff in all manner from move and melee slow to base resists to dispell to shadowstep even.<br>
<br>
Combine that with a wis class with offense and heals like a shammy  or druid and you have a team you simply cannot kill and will kill you if you overextend. Selo   a healer is scary, combine the pure offense a druid and shammy can dish out and you got something far worse.<br>
<br>
If safe is not your main concern you could swap the wis out for a pure killer like an sk, necro, wiz whatever class is the current kill champ after the next round of balances/nerfs. That's less safe but hell they can kill people so fast that no one can react.<br>
<br>
when talking about 2 people why stop there? a group is 6, get 2 bards and a raid of 12 or 3 bards for a raid of 18 or... etc.<br>
<br>
Line up any 5 heal   kill of your choice and the only class worth filling that 6th slot is a smart well geared bard. Nothing else even comes close to the synergy 5 good pvp players can choose other than the bard because the way songs work with groups and their basically unique nature.<br>
<br>
<br>
So then what's the point of all this? People hate that bards are super support and their inability to actually hurt a bard means said bard can talk trash to them alllllllllllll day. Ask occ =)<br>
<br>
How come bards are leaders in points? well lets see you log on and whatever core group you know of hardened killers says ok come to zone x we need a bard. Hell who says only one group bothered to ask?<br>
<br>
I'll give you a useless little story (oh story time with liq - how novel).<br>
<br>
When I took my forced break from eq years ago I played diablo2 for a month or so. I played amazons which used the Bow based strafe skill to auto aim insane number of arrows into things. After my 3rd level 75 zon each tweaked to how I learned the game, I was friends with all the other zons in us west server.<br>
<br>
So I thought about it and the communal bank was full of trash items that no one in their right mind would wear except ebay to clueless people.. those items had skill   mods on them...<br>
<br>
So I made a paly, which in diablo had auras like well bard songs in eq. long story shorter this Milquetoast of a paly only did one thing... work on his concentrate skill which with after all those trash items , made  group damage do 500% of their base damage... one zon became like 5, 2 +  Liq's suck ass paly = 10 zons.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, the instant I hit the &quot;hell&quot; level at level 18 piggy backed onto other zons made expressly for the occasion I was level 75 almost instantly because as I logged on the zons would start a bidding war for who got the paly.<br>
<br>
So eventually we took the show on to pvp. All my paly did was follow the zons and all they did was light up hapless pvp people (no ambushes) like Christmas trees with god level auto aiming strafe.<br>
<br>
Oh man how people wanted palys nerfed even tho the paly himself (the complete wimp) couldn;t kill a damn thing in the highest level.<br>
<br>
When I stopped playing diablo 2 I donated all my toons to the zon community and all they really wanted was the paly since they all had their own zons.<br>
<br>
<br>
So here come the mucho lame ideas that you find on the eqlive board. People resent the sheer power bards can lend their groupmates in pvp pure and simple. Therefore they think up outlandish ideas that make anyone even remotely thinking, well laugh.<br>
<br>
So yes very funny thread. I still cannot see how the core kill classes still haven;t gotten balanced.<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
-Liq<br>
